# Cloudflare Pages _redirects — SPA client-side routing fallback.
#
# Every unknown path returns 200 + index.html so the SvelteKit router
# resolves the route on the client. Without this, navigating directly to
# `/brief/2026-05-24` would return Pages' default 404 because the static
# build has no per-route HTML files (adapter-static `fallback: 'index.html'`
# only handles unmatched routes during build, not at deploy-time fetch).
#
# The API is reached cross-origin via VITE_API_BASE (set in CF Pages
# project env vars). Proxying /api/* through Pages was the alternative —
# rejected because it adds ~30 ms latency per request and hides CORS
# behaviour. See apps/web/README.md for the deploy topology.
#
# IMPORTANT: `/_app/*` MUST be excluded from the SPA fallback. CF Pages
# treats those URLs as immutable hashed assets and applies a long-cache
# response header (~4h). When a stale browser tab requests an old chunk
# hash that no longer exists in the deploy, falling back to index.html
# means the CDN poisons that URL with cached HTML under a JS content-type
# expectation — every subsequent request (including hard refresh) returns
# the cached HTML, breaking the module loader with
# "Failed to load module script: Expected a JavaScript-or-Wasm module
# script but the server responded with a MIME type of text/html" and a
# blank-screen SPA. Returning 404 for missing chunks lets SvelteKit's
# stale-import recovery (handleError + auto-reload) do its job.
/_app/*  /_app/:splat  404
/*  /index.html  200
